Description: Oracle Database Programming Interface Oracle Database Programming Interface for C (ODPI-C) is an open source library of C code that simplifies access to Oracle Database for applications written in C or C++. It is a wrapper over Oracle Call Interface (OCI) that makes applications and language interfaces easier to develop. . ODPI-C supports basic and advanced features of Oracle Database and Oracle Client. See the homepage for a list.
Package-List: libodpic4 deb contrib/libs optional arch=any odpic-dev deb contrib/libdevel optional arch=any odpic-doc deb contrib/doc optional arch=all
